Success rate each season¶

In [7]:
for i in data.season.unique():
    Y = data.loc[data['season']==i]
    f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5,5))
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    total=Y.count().max()
    graph = sns.countplot(y=Y['termination_reason']).set_title("Success in season %s"%i)
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.text(p.get_width()+6, p.get_y()+p.get_height()/2, '%d %%' %(int(p.get_width())*100/int(total)) ,fontsize=10, color='blue', ha='left', va='center')
    plt.show()

top_5_climbs = data.groupby('peak_name', as_index=False).agg({'peak_id' : 'count'}).sort_values(by='peak_id', ascending=False).head()
top_5_climbs.rename(columns={'peak_id' : 'count'},inplace=True)
f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6,6))
sns.set(style="whitegrid")
graph = sns.barplot(x='peak_name', y = 'count', data=top_5_climbs).set_title("Top 5 climbs")
for p in ax.patches:
    ax.text(p.get_x()+0.5*p.get_width(), p.get_height()+15, '%d'%p.get_height(),fontsize=12, color='blue', ha='center', va='center')
plt.show()

    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.text(p.get_width()+6, p.get_y()+p.get_height()/2, '%d %%' %(int(p.get_width())*100/int(total)) ,fontsize=10, color='blue', ha='left', va='center')

Top Trekking companies¶

In [15]:
data['new']=""
def main(x):
    if x =='Success (main peak)':
        y=1
    else:
        y=0
    return(y)
data['new']=data['termination_reason'].apply(lambda x:main(x))
Trekking_company = data.groupby('trekking_agency',as_index=False).agg({'peak_id' : 'count', 'new':'sum'}).sort_values(by='peak_id',ascending=False)
Trekking_company['Successrate']=Trekking_company['new']*100/Trekking_company['peak_id']
Trekking_company.rename(columns={'peak_id' : 'total_treks', 'new' : 'succesfull_summits'}, inplace=True)
Trekking_company.head(10)

Death rate with respect to peak¶

In [23]:
data['death']=data['member_deaths']+data['hired_staff_deaths']
death_by_peak = data.groupby('peak_name',as_index=False).agg({'death' : 'sum'}).sort_values(by='death', ascending=False)
f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5,90))
sns.set(style="whitegrid")
graph = sns.barplot(y='peak_name', x = 'death', data=death_by_peak)
plt.show()
In [35]:
death_per  = data[['peak_name','members','death']].groupby('peak_name',as_index=False).agg({'members' : 'sum', 'death' : 'sum'})
death_per['death_percent']=death_per['death']/death_per['members']
death_per.sort_values(by='death_percent',ascending=False, inplace=True)
f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5,90))
sns.set(style="whitegrid")
graph = sns.barplot(y='peak_name', x = 'death_percent', data=death_per)
plt.show()
